@jay_venturaaaa suicide, depression, and isolation are very sad. 
Toxic masculinity is a horrible thing that hurts men too. Which the commercial commented on as well. This isn't just about sexual harassment or rape. It's also about the toxic views of masculinity that prevent men from having healthy emotional discussions. Reaching out for professional help without being seen as a "pussy". Men and boys not being bullied or mocked for not fitting traditional male stereotypes. That's ALL toxic masculinity and all of it needs to stop. 
Why not go help with that rather than troll the internet for women to blame your problems on.

@jay_venturaaaa the commercial did none of that...unless you think "masculine" means bullying, sexual harassment of women, and aggression. 
In which case, fuck yes. That should be attacked and done away with.

And if you don't want to be painted with the same brush, take the message of the commercial to heart. Don't be toxic or be a bystander, stand up and stop those who perpetrate toxic masculine behavior. Simple.
